# Build context for the `api` service is the repo root (see docker-compose.yml:
# api → context: .). The api Dockerfile only needs `api/` + `VERSION`, so keep
# everything else out of the context that gets shipped to the builder. This
# shrinks the build, speeds it up, and avoids needless disk churn on small
# brain boxes. Other services build from their own sub-contexts (ui → ./ui,
# nodeos → ./nodeos, public-chat → ./apps/public-chat) and are unaffected.

# VCS + editor
.git
.gitignore
.pytest_cache
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
*.swp

# Other service trees (their own build contexts — not needed by the api image)
ui
nodeos
apps
vector-db

# Repo content not needed at runtime in the api image
scripts
tests
notes
docs
export
input_samples
brain-apps
ops
# NOTE: deliberately NOT excluding "*.md" — the api image needs
# api/brain_persona.template.md + api/brain_persona_nous.md (COPY api /app/api).
# Root-level .md files are KB-sized; not worth risking the persona files.

# Secrets + local/runtime artifacts (defense in depth — never in an image)
.env
.env.*
docker-compose.override.yml
api/brain_persona.local.md
